title: I cannot find Wi-Fi signals. What should I do?
answer:
If you have enabled Wi-Fi on your phone, but it cannot find Wi-Fi signals from a wireless router while other devices can, perform the following operations:


l Verify that the wireless router's service set identifier (SSID) is not hidden. 

l Verify that your phone is within the Wi-Fi coverage of the wireless router. 

l Disable and then enable Wi-Fi on your phone. 

l Restart your phone.
